// resilience4j.circuitbreaker.instances.market-data.failure-rate-threshold=50

// ANSWER: If all 3 retries fail → circuit breaker counts 1 FAILURE
// The @Retry block (inner) exhausts all retries and throws.
// That SINGLE exception is what @CircuitBreaker (outer) counts.
// So 3 retry attempts = 1 circuit breaker failure event.
class Explanation {
    static void explain() {
        System.out.println("3 retries exhausted = 1 circuit breaker failure");
    }
}

